Mohammadh Sayed said he has instructed his legal team to engage with police and the National Prosecuting Authority daily, to ensure justice for his son prevails. Courtesy of #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - The father of a young patient who died last year has denied any involvement in the murder of Doctor Abdullay Munshi. Mohammadh Sayed said he has instructed his legal team to engage with police and the National Prosecuting Authority daily, to ensure justice for his son prevails. READ: Medical fraternity calls for justice after doctor is killed Munshi and Professor Peter Beale were on trial for culpable homicide after Sayed's son, Zayyaan, died last year following medical complications. The anesthesiologist was gunned down on Wednesday in Orange Grove, Johannesburg, in an apparent hit.